# V3 Phase 7 — SPA fallback for Cloudflare Pages and Netlify.
#
# When the cloud-mode bundle is hosted on a static CDN, every deep
# link must resolve to `index.html` because TanStack Router is a pure
# client-side router. Cloudflare Pages' default behaviour already does
# this, but making the rule explicit protects against ingress
# configurations that strip the default.

/app/*  /app/index.html  200
/*      /index.html      200
